      "span_text": "Dried marigold petals and marigold concentrates were used as feed additives to improve the pigmentation of the poultry skin and the eggs of laying hens  pumpkin pulp was 9.68%, similar with the value registered for the mixture AFC 1, but with the crude fiber (0.84%) and crude fat (0.83%) lower then the ones obtained for AFC 1."
